<item>
            <title>[MATH-458] Interpolators: Remove &quot;MathException&quot; from the signature of the &quot;interpolate&quot; method</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-458</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The interfaces for the interpolators contain a &quot;throws&quot; clause that should be removed.&lt;br/&gt;
E.g.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt; UnivariateRealInterpolator {

    /**
     * Computes an interpolating function &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the data set.
     * @param xval the arguments &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the interpolation points
     * @param yval the values &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the interpolation points
     * @&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; a function which interpolates the data set
     * @&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; MathException &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; arguments violate assumptions made by the
     *         interpolation algorithm
     */
    UnivariateRealFunction interpolate(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; xval[], &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;double&lt;/span&gt; yval[])
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;throws&lt;/span&gt; MathException;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assumptions violation should be dealt with by throwing appropriate unchecked exceptions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
